      "description": "This E46 M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. Power is managed through a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission and delivered to the rear wheels via a variable M-differential lock. The chassis has been maintained with technical rigor, including proactive rod bearing replacement and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural integrity under lateral load. The suspension remains tight, preserving the 50/50 weight distribution and communicative steering rack that define this chassis. Recent service includes a valve adjustment and fresh fluids, ensuring the powerplant pulls cleanly to its 8,000 RPM redline.",
